**Security Rule:** Users must be notified of suspicious authentication attempts, whether successful or not, such as logins from an unusual location or client or a success following several failures.

**Vulnerability Pattern (Description):** The application never alerts users to anomalous logins, so an account takeover from a new device or country goes completely unnoticed.

**Secure Pattern (Description):** Authentication events are evaluated for risk signals, and the user is sent an out-of-band notification when a login looks suspicious.

