**Security Rule:** Users must be notified after changes to their authentication details, including credential resets and changes to the username or email address.

**Vulnerability Pattern (Description):** A password reset or email change is applied silently, so a victim of account takeover gets no warning that their credentials were altered.

**Secure Pattern (Description):** Any change to a credential or to the username or email triggers an out-of-band notification, sent to the previous contact address when an email is being changed.

