**Security Rule:** Valid usernames must not be inferable from failed authentication, and registration and forgot-password flows must give identical responses, status codes, and timing whether or not an account exists.

**Vulnerability Pattern (Description):** Login, registration, or password reset reveals account existence through a distinct error message, HTTP status, or noticeably different response time, enabling username enumeration.

**Secure Pattern (Description):** These flows return a single generic message and status regardless of whether the account exists, and run the same work so response timing does not leak existence.

