**Security Rule:** When a multi-factor authentication factor is lost, identity proofing must be repeated at the same assurance level used during the original enrollment.

**Vulnerability Pattern (Description):** A lost second factor can be replaced with only a weak self-service check, so an attacker who controls the recovery channel re-enrolls their own device.

**Secure Pattern (Description):** Re-enrolling a replacement factor requires identity proofing equivalent to the original enrollment, rather than a lower-assurance shortcut.

[[CSHARP PATTERNS]]
Vulnerable:
```
void ReplaceMfa(User u) => EnrollTotp(u);
```
Secure:
```
void ReplaceMfa(User u, Proofing p) {
    if (p.Level < u.EnrollmentProofingLevel)
        throw new UnauthorizedAccessException("re-proofing required");
    EnrollTotp(u);
}
```

[[GENERIC PATTERNS]]
Vulnerable:
```
if email_link_clicked(user): enroll_new_factor(user)
```
Secure:
```
if proofing_level(recovery) >= proofing_level(enrollment):
    enroll_new_factor(user)
```

