    if proofing_result.level < user.enrollment_proofing_level:
        raise PermissionError("re-proofing required")
    enroll_totp(user)
```

**Security Rule:** Administrators may start a password reset for a user, but must not be able to set or choose that user's password, so an administrator never knows a user's credential.

**Vulnerability Pattern (Description):** An admin function sets a user's password directly to a value the admin picks, meaning the administrator knows the user's password and can impersonate them.

**Secure Pattern (Description):** Admin recovery only triggers a self-service reset flow, sending the user a one-time link so the user alone chooses the new password.

