**Security Rule:** A code-based out-of-band authentication mechanism must be protected against brute force with rate limiting, and ideally use a code with at least 64 bits of entropy.

**Vulnerability Pattern (Description):** Unlimited verification attempts are allowed against a short numeric code, so an attacker can iterate the entire code space in seconds.

**Secure Pattern (Description):** Verification attempts are rate limited per code and per account, and the code is invalidated after a small number of failures.

[[CSHARP PATTERNS]]
Vulnerable:
```
bool Verify(User u, string submitted) =>
    submitted == _otpStore[u.Id];
```
Secure:
```
bool Verify(string requestId, string submitted) {
    if (_tries.Increment(requestId) > 5) {
        _otpStore.Invalidate(requestId);
        throw new TooManyRequestsException();
    }
    return submitted == _otpStore[requestId];
}
```

