**Security Rule:** Users must be able to view their currently active sessions and, after authenticating again with at least one factor, terminate any or all of them.

**Vulnerability Pattern (Description):** Users have no way to see where they are logged in or to revoke other sessions, so a user who suspects compromise cannot evict the attacker themselves.

