**Security Rule:** Highly sensitive transactions or operations must require further authentication with at least one factor, or a secondary verification step, before they are carried out.

**Vulnerability Pattern (Description):** A high-value operation such as a large transfer or a destructive administrative action proceeds on the strength of the existing session alone, so a hijacked session can perform it unchecked.

